commit.message: Update outdated static file loader tags in memory_panel.html to support Django 3.0
Use is_alive instead of isAlive for Python 3.9 compatibility.

Update documentation of compatible Python versions

Include untracked container objects in summary

Container objects (like simple dicts) were missing from the summary diff
if those are not tracked by the garbage collector due to type-specific
optimizations. More info here:

https://docs.python.org/3/library/gc.html#gc.is_tracked

Fixes issue #97

Fix class names in summary output on Python 3.x

Use a regular expression with a group to cut off the prefix and suffix
of a type representation. The previous implementation would cut off the
suffix even if the prefix didn't match, leading to weird looking output.

Fixes #98

Fix generator test on Python 3.8

The size of a "fresh" generator appears to be slightly smaller than a
generator in use - at least on Python 3.8. Change the test to compare
the generator size in later iterations.

Update asizeof.py (#88)

The `stats` now include a list of _up to_ 100 largest objects ranked by _total size_ and controlled by new options `above` and `cutoff` for all non-zero `stats` values.

Specify the `stats` and `cutoff` values separately.  But `stats` with _fractional_ `cutoff` values are still supported for backward compatibility.

New `Asizer` properties `cutoff` and `ranked` and new method `exclude_objs` to exclude the given objects from sizing, profiling and ranking.  The latter is also used to avoid sizing most (but not all) `asizeof` internal, private objects.

Modified handling of the `seen` property, now set _before_ sizing an object to avoid duplicate sizing if referenced.

Fixed sizing of generators and generator expressions while keeping the generator intact, i.e. preserving its integrity.  The `test_generator` test case required an update.
